04/01/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The UNDP in Macedonia is continuing a project aimed at reducing unemployment among young people, co-ordinator Vladimir Kuculovski announced on Wednesday (January 3rd).
The UNDP is seeking to actively encourage the hiring of young people in the private sector.
The five-month initiative covers 20 Macedonian municipalities.
Last year it was oriented mainly towards highly educated youth.
This year, the focus is on those with a secondary school education.
(Dnevnik - 04/01/07;
Telma TV - 03/01/07)
